			<p class="padding-top">Strong adjectives are considered grammatically strong as they have more
				inflectional endings than weak nouns. If you have difficulty remembering the endings,
				consider the endings you learned for strong nouns and demonstratives. For example,
				compare the strong masculine accusative demonstrative
				'<em>&thorn;o<strong>-ne</strong></em>' and the masculine accusative adjective ending
				'<strong>-ne</strong>', or the feminine genitive and dative demonstrative
				'<em>&thorn;&aelig;<strong>-re</strong></em>' and the feminine genitive and dative demonstrative
